# [[ project_name ]] (mobile)

Expo SDK 55 app (React Native 0.83, New Architecture) with Expo Router, TypeScript, and Tamagui. It renders to native via EAS and to web via React Native Web with Expo Router static rendering, deployed to Vercel.

## Develop

```sh
npm install
npm run start      # native dev (press i / a), or
npm run web        # React Native Web in the browser
```

Copy the repo `.env.example` to `.env` and set the public values. Only `EXPO_PUBLIC_*` vars reach the device:

- `EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`
- `EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` (the `sb_publishable_*` key, client-safe)
- `EXPO_PUBLIC_APP_ENV` (`develop` | `preview` | `prod`; drives the env badge)

The `sb_secret_*` key is server-only and never belongs in an `EXPO_PUBLIC_` var.

## Auth and session storage

Sessions persist through an encrypted adapter (`src/lib/secure-storage.ts`): a per-key AES key in `expo-secure-store`, the encrypted session in `AsyncStorage`. This sidesteps the 2048-byte SecureStore item limit. On web, supabase-js uses its default browser storage.

## Heavy compute

`src/lib/heavy-compute.ts` calls a Supabase Edge Function (`run-heavy`) that wraps a Modal HTTPS endpoint. The Modal secret stays server-side and never ships in the bundle.

## Web export and Vercel

```sh
npm run export:web   # writes the static site to dist/
```

Deploy `dist/` to Vercel as a static output.

## Native builds (EAS)

```sh
npx eas build --profile development --platform ios
npx eas build --profile preview --platform android
npx eas build --profile production --platform all
```

Native builds and the EAS profiles require the EAS cloud toolchain; they do not run in a plain container.
